&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Our mission is to seek out areas of social need and policy failure and make transformational change using design and technology. We believe that government, organisations and businesses can be a force of good but there can be a gap between their understanding of, and ability to meet the expectations of those needing positive change. Our job is to use design, technology and production to narrow the gap between those with the power and responsibility to make a positive change, and those who need it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;If you’d like to join us but didn’t see a current job vacancy that meets your skill set or interest, or are interested in an internship, please submit your details below. Every week we receive requests to meet our team members to discuss career opportunities, which makes it difficult to respond to them all. Our advice — if you are looking for a role or career advice — is reach out directly to someone you know at Portable and/or come along to one of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.portable.com.au/events/&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;our regular events&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; to connect.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to submit your application:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We might not have the perfect role for you yet, but we’ll keep your application on file for when the role becomes available.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;To apply send us your resume and cover letter answering the following questions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;What job do you wish we had available for you?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Why Portable is right for you, and why are you right for Portable?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Provide an example of your work. This could be your portfolio, links to websites you played a role in creating or a written description of your role in recent projects &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Portable&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care about people and the world. We look for areas of social need and policy failure and make transformational change using research, design and technology. Our clients are as passionate as we are, working in government agencies, nonprofit organisations and socially-minded businesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are currently 65+ of us working as researchers, strategists, designers, technologists and producers from our head office in Collingwood, and remotely from co-working spaces and homes across Australia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then there’s you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A principal technologist with range&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is part of one of our delivery teams. The work covers multiple projects at once: different clients, different problem spaces, different technology environments. You won’t be embedded with a single client long-term. You’ll move across a portfolio of work, going where you’re needed and demonstrating excellence in all these areas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That requires genuine adaptability. One week you might be leading architecture decisions on a cloud-native platform and the next, you’re pairing with a mid-level developer on a tricky integration, or helping shape a proposal. You’re comfortable with that kind of context-switching and even enjoy it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re past the point of needing to prove yourself technically. What drives you is doing the work properly: building the right thing, making sure the team understands why, and leaving things in better shape than you found them. You can walk into an ambiguous situation, work out what’s needed, and get on with it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You also know that good technology consulting isn’t only about delivery. You help us win work by being someone clients trust, and by being able to articulate the technical approach clearly when it matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for someone who:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is a principal-level practitioner: technically strong, adaptable across stacks, and able to lead projects independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brings depth in C#, Python, Typescript, AWS and/or Azure, paired with a technology-agnostic mindset and willingness to work across open source and Microsoft ecosystems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is across AI tooling and applies it actively, both in their own work and to help their team work better&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has designed and delivered complex systems across multiple projects and industries, from architecture through to production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can lead delivery independently: scoping work, managing uncertainty and keeping teams on track&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicates clearly with a wide range of stakeholders, in person and in writing, without hiding behind jargon&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentors more junior staff through pairing, pull request reviews and direct guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shares knowledge freely and makes the people around them better&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helps us grow by contributing to pitches and building client trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A week at Portable might look like:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading architecture and implementation of a new API layer on an AWS-hosted platform, while reviewing infrastructure decisions on a separate Azure engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pairing with a mid-level engineer on a complex integration problem, not just solving it but helping them understand the reasoning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing pull requests across a couple of active projects, with feedback that improves both the code and the person who wrote it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to a proposal, helping the team frame the technical approach and make the case for why Portable is the right partner&lt;/li&gt;
